#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/binary_distribution.py:docstring of
#: spack.binary_distribution.BinaryCacheIndex:1
msgid ""
"The BinaryCacheIndex tracks what specs are available on (usually remote) "
"binary caches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/binary_distribution.py:docstring of
#: spack.binary_distribution.BinaryCacheIndex:4
msgid ""
"This index is \"best effort\", in the sense that whenever we don't find what "
"we're looking for here, we will attempt to fetch it directly from configured "
"mirrors anyway.  Thus, it has the potential to speed things up, but cache "
"misses shouldn't break any spack functionality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/binary_distribution.py:docstring of
#: spack.binary_distribution.BinaryCacheIndex:9
msgid ""
"At the moment, everything in this class is initialized as lazily as "
"possible, so that it avoids slowing anything in spack down until absolutely "
"necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/binary_distribution.py:docstring of
#: spack.binary_distribution.BinaryCacheIndex:13
msgid ""
"TODO: What's the cost if, e.g., we realize in the middle of a spack install "
"that the cache is out of date, and we fetch directly?  Does it mean we "
"should have paid the price to update the cache earlier?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/binary_distribution.py:docstring of
#: spack.binary_distribution.BinaryCacheIndex.clear:1
