#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:3
msgid "***The Package class***"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:5
msgid ""
"At its core, a package consists of a set of software to be installed. A "
"package may focus on a piece of software and its associated software "
"dependencies or it may simply be a set, or bundle, of software.  The former "
"requires defining how to fetch, verify (via, e.g., sha256), build, and "
"install that software and the packages it depends on, so that dependencies "
"can be installed along with the package itself.   The latter, sometimes "
"referred to as a ``no-source`` package, requires only defining the packages "
"to be built."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:14
msgid "Packages are written in pure Python."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:16
msgid "There are two main parts of a Spack package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:18
msgid ""
"**The package class**.  Classes contain ``directives``, which are special "
"functions, that add metadata (versions, patches, dependencies, and other "
"information) to packages (see ``directives.py``). Directives provide the "
"constraints that are used as input to the concretizer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:23
msgid ""
"**Package instances**. Once instantiated, a package can be passed to the "
"PackageInstaller. It calls methods like ``do_stage()`` on the ``Package`` "
"object, and it uses those to drive user-implemented methods like "
"``patch()``, ``install()``, and other build steps. To install software, an "
"instantiated package needs a *concrete* spec, which guides the behavior of "
"the various install methods."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:29
msgid "Packages are imported from repos (see ``repo.py``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:31
msgid "**Package DSL**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:33
msgid ""
"Look in ``lib/spack/docs`` or check https://spack.readthedocs.io for the "
"full documentation of the package domain-specific language.  That used to be "
"partially documented here, but as it grew, the docs here became increasingly "
"out of date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:38
msgid "**Package Lifecycle**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:40
msgid "A package's lifecycle over a run of Spack looks something like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:42
msgid ""
"p = Package()             # Done for you by spack\n"
"\n"
"p.do_fetch()              # downloads tarball from a URL (or VCS)\n"
"p.do_stage()              # expands tarball in a temp directory\n"
"p.do_patch()              # applies patches to expanded source\n"
"p.do_uninstall()          # removes install directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:51
msgid ""
"although packages that do not have code have nothing to fetch so omit ``p."
"do_fetch()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:54
msgid "There are also some other commands that clean the build area:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:56
msgid ""
"p.do_clean()              # removes the stage directory entirely\n"
"p.do_restage()            # removes the build directory and\n"
"                          # re-expands the archive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:62
msgid ""
"The convention used here is that a ``do_*`` function is intended to be "
"called internally by Spack commands (in ``spack.cmd``).  These aren't for "
"package writers to override, and doing so may break the functionality of the "
"Package class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package_base.py:docstring of
#: spack.package_base.PackageBase:67
